School starts 1 week from today! We can't wait to see you!

We will be having a drive thru open house on Monday, August 24th from 5-6 pm . There is a map attached below of where your child's classroom teacher will be located on the grounds. Please follow the traffic arrows so there is not a traffic jam. Parents and students will remain in their cars. Teachers will hand out an information sheet and say hello. This will be a quick meet your teacher time.

Elementary students can give their teacher classroom supplies at open house. Middle school teacher's have asked middle school students to bring their supplies the first day of class on Aug. 25th.

If anyone would like to drop your child's school supplies off this week, you may do so through Thursday from 8:30 -12:30.

I apologize that you will have to turn your phone to see the picture.

post_text:
Good afternoon Westview Families! Governor Parsons announced today that all Missouri schools will remain closed for the rest of the year BUT they must continue their services through the end of the regular school year.

What does this mean for Westview? We will continue the packets and food distribution through May 8th. (Our last calendar day.) All packets are still required to be completed each week and grades/attendance will be taken as we have the last few weeks. We will send out more information in the coming weeks on picking up any items left at school.

The school buildings must remain closed.

post_text: Good evening! This is just a reminder that new packets will be delivered tomorrow starting at 11 am. Please make sure the work from last week is hanging on the mailbox, so we can make a quick exchange. If you are sending your work electronically, remember it is due tomorrow. No late work is being accepted. Please make sure your name is on every paper. We hope everyone is safe and well! If you are experiencing any symptoms of the Corona virus, please contact your child's teacher and we will require alternate ways of completing work. Stay safe.

Bus B route will start at the normal time.

post_text:
Congratulations 👏 to Miss Cloie our para, Barbara Duncan one of our awesome kitchen ladies, and Mrs. Macy our brilliant kindergarten teacher! They were each voted as staff of the Week throughout November.
Miss Cloie begins each student's day with a bright smile as she plays upbeat songs and dances with the kids every morning during parent drop off! 🎵🎶
Miss Barbara is a humble servant. Never without a kind word or gesture. She is a kind spirit that can't be beat!🍎
And Mrs. Macy is a master at her craft! The students say she is nice, kind, and always make learning as fun as possible.
We are very THANKFUL for you ALL!
